  </category>

  <!-- ========== PATTERN 5: LACE OF COUNTRY STREETS ========== -->
  <category>
    <pattern>LACE OF COUNTRY STREETS</pattern>
    <template>
      <think>
        <set name="current_pattern">5</set>
        <set name="pattern_name">LACE OF COUNTRY STREETS</set>
        <set name="confidence">1</set>
      </think>
      <b>Pattern 5: LACE OF COUNTRY STREETS *</b>

      <b>Problem:</b> The suburb is an obsolete and contradictory form of
      human settlement.

      <b>Solution:</b> In the zone where city and country meet:
      - Place country roads at least 1 mile apart
      - Enclose squares of countryside at least 1 square mile
      - Build homesteads along roads, one lot deep
      - Minimum lot size: half an acre
      - Open countryside behind the houses

      <b>Key Numbers:</b> ~400 households per square mile, ~1600 people

      <condition name="show_connections" value="true">
        <b>Preceding:</b> <srai>PATTERN NAME 3</srai>
        <b>Following:</b> <srai>LIST FOLLOWING PATTERNS 5</srai>
      </condition>
    </template>
  </category>

